text: Jean Evelyn Headberry (1911–1993) was an Australian registered nurse and midwife who was awarded the Florence Nightingale Medal in 1961. Headberry served as an Army nurse during World War II. Headberry was awarded a Centaur Memorial Scholarship in 1946 to study in England. She later became the Dean of Royal Melbourne and Associated Hospital's School of Nursing. ==References== * https://www.loc.gov/rr/frd/Military_Law/pdf/RC_May-1962.pdf * https://trove.nla.gov.au/newspaper/result?q=Jean+Headberry Category:1911 births Category:1993 deaths Category:Australian nurses Category:World War II nurses Category:Australian midwives Category:Florence Nightingale Medal recipients
